The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) and their tractable classes, which are typically studied in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The concept of symmetry breaking is also relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of lexleader constraints and their impact on the number of solutions is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
